Friends and loved ones say Lane Britnell benefited greatly from his prescribed medical marijuana and that he does not deserve to go to jail.</description><source>Top stories sidebar</source><pubDate>Tue, 03 Nov 2015 12:18:01 Z</pubDate><enclosure url="http://www.canada.com/cms/binary/11488911.jpg" type="image/jpeg" /></item><item><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:www.canada.com:content=11487452</guid><link>http://www.canada.com/news/saskatoon/real+estate+fraudster+admits+scamming+saskatchewan+victims/11487452/story.html</link><title>Real estate fraudster admits scamming Saskatchewan victims of $1.2 million</title><description>More than a dozen investors were lined up to testify this week about how much money Joshua Douglas Johnston took from them, but they no longer have to, after Johnston said he wouldn&#8217;t dispute the amount of the fraud anymore &#8212; all $1.2 million of it. Johnston&#8217;s sentencing hearing was set for four days this week, but when it began on Monday in Saskatoon provincial court, Johnston, who didn&#8217;t have a lawyer with him in court, said he didn&#8217;t want to &#8220;drag this out any longer.&#8221; He said he plans to transfer to Saskatoon&#160;similar charges that he faces in Alberta, so that he can be sentenced on everything all at once.</description><source>Top stories sidebar</source><pubDate>Tue, 03 Nov 2015 02:21:17 Z</pubDate><enclosure url="http://www.canada.com/cms/binary/8389465.jpg" type="image/jpeg" /></item><item><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:www.canada.com:content=11487451</guid><link>http://www.canada.com/news/saskatoon/relaxed+rules+riverfront+patios+backed/11487451/story.html</link><title>Relaxed rules for riverfront patios backed</title><description>The City of Saskatoon is moving to make it easier to take in a view of the river while enjoying a cocktail downtown. City staff are proposing changes that would remove restrictions on outdoor patios connected to restaurants along Spadina Crescent from the University Bridge to the Broadway Bridge.</description><source>Top stories sidebar</source><pubDate>Tue, 03 Nov 2015 02:21:14 Z</pubDate><enclosure url="http://www.canada.com/cms/binary/11294837.jpg" type="image/jpeg" /></item></channel></rss>
